  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Key Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18 to 65 years of age

          -  Diagnosed with subjective tinnitus due to hearing loss with at least some tonal
             quality of the tinnitus.

          -  Diagnosis of tinnitus for at least one year

          -  Tinnitus severity of 18 or greater on TRQ cross checked with TQ severity of Grade 3 or
             worse

        Key Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Acute or intermittent tinnitus

          -  Severe hearing loss

          -  History of significant ear disease such as Meniere's disease, ear tumors, or evidence
             of active middle ear disease.

          -  Any other implanted device
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
